'63','','1','JackS','211.94.154.80','agentfactory@hotmail.com','','Dear Matt:\n    \n      I am very interested in what you said after I read your paper. But there is something wrong with me, and I cann\'t catch any job printing . I had downloaded the Hijetter.exe program and added the \"@PJL DEFAULT HOLD=STORE\" command in the program after  \" PFTses-&gt;write_ustatus(\"OFF\");\" with my own function. But I cann\'t find the \"0:savedevicesavedJobsHeldJob\" directory on my printer . My printer is HP LaserJet 5200 , and I don\'t know which type you tested on and how  do you add the  \"@PJL DEFAULT HOLD=STORE\" command in the Hijetter.exe program . \n \n     Thanks very much, waiting for your reply!','2011-06-12 20:48:09','2011-06-13 01:48:09','0','0','110','','0'),(
