'69','','1','Matt','71.63.150.135','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@Matthew:  Okay.. I\'m callin\' BS on this one unless you give me some more info on how this is actually working.  ;-)\n\nThat said, I REALLY want to be proven wrong.  My big question right now is:\n\nHow are you determining the difference between *distros*?  I mean, the stack is the same in kernel 2.6.whatever, regardless of distro.. so how are you differentiating between them?\n\nI think showing that no packets are being sniffed in Wireshark is kind of misleading.. I mean, okay.. it doesn\'t generate any TCP traffic.. but that leaves a lot of other protocols that it could be using.\n\nMy other question.. is this specifically an issue with VMware?  I watched the video with the volume down, so if you mentioned this in the video, I appologize.\n\nIf you don\'t want to post info about this publicly, feel free to email me.  I\'m definitely interested in this one.','2010-06-23 21:16:23','2010-06-24 02:16:23','0','68','167','','2'),(
'70','','1','Matt','71.63.150.135','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@Matthew:  I just read the description of the video.. where you specify that it doesn\'t use any layer 3 protocols.. so, I\'m guessing it\'s ARP based.. but still trying to figure out how you would differentiate between distros using ARP...','2010-06-23 21:22:44','2010-06-24 02:22:44','0','69','167','','2');
