'188','','1','Matt','71.63.150.135','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','Thanks for the comment!\n\nI always find it encouraging to know that people find my write-ups useful/interesting.  It\'s also nice to know that people are able to make it through the posts, as I sometimes wonder if I\'m overdoing it, yanno?  :-)\n\nAlso.. I\'m open to ideas for future posts.  If you have something that you think other people might find useful, or would like to know more about yourself, PLEASE let me know.  \n\nAnd, if you like my stories.. check out Synjunkie\'s blog.  He\'s got some Bob stories that have kind of fueled my fire.  He\'s also a bit more methodical than I am.  :-)\n\n<a href=\"http://synjunkie.blogspot.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://synjunkie.blogspot.com</a>','2010-05-26 16:02:20','2010-05-26 21:02:20','0','187','267','','2'),(
'189','','1','Erik','68.58.182.249','fakeforareason@gmail.com','http://n/a','Anytime man, you\'re definitely not overdoing it.  They keep me awake while I\'m at work :-p\n\nHonestly I\'m open to learning anything and everything about security. I can\'t really think of anything specific.  The social engineering items always hit home as a webmaster as we\'re constantly getting hit by attempts via email (though they\'re usually blunt about needing a password, not as evasive as your techniques). \n\nI\'m a recent graduate, and I\'m trying to self teach myself as much about security auditing / pen testing, as well as securing personal/enterprise networks. So really...i\'ll take anything haha. \n\nI\'ll let you know if I come up with something good - take it easy.','2010-05-26 20:21:37','2010-05-27 01:21:37','0','0','267','','0'),(
'190','','1','Sie','20.138.1.245','vickers.j.simon@sky.com','','I agree with Erik, have been following this blog with interest since I picked up the link from Synjunkies site. Very well written and interesting information to take away.\n\nAlways good to read \'real worldy\' example rather than just being told you can run X to get get Y.\n\nAny chance of a link to a good email headers article/write up? IE What\'s what? I get the generals I just like to know the who\'s and why =)','2010-05-27 03:49:00','2010-05-27 08:49:00','0','0','267','','0'),(
