'230','','1','Matt','70.89.197.145','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','Back when I hacked, I did it as part of a team.. whereas now, I\'m on my own.  I see benefits in both.\n\nDoing it as a team made the process faster, but you really, really had to trust who you were working with.  I tend to be really anal about cleaning up logs, erasing my tracks, not doing attacks that generate a lot of noise.. whereas others in my previous teams were not as anal as I was.  This caused a lot of frustration.  However, I have worked with really good teams that were as clean as I was and being able to brainstorm and combine data and ideas really helped.\n\nWorking on my own takes more time, but I\'m able to ensure that I\'m not leaving a trail.  So, ultimately, it really depends.\n\nI think in the penetration testing world, where getting caught doesn\'t mean prison time, working as a team is great.. but it ultimately comes down to personal preference.','2010-06-08 08:30:01','2010-06-08 13:30:01','0','229','291','','2'),(
