'253','','1','Matt','70.89.197.145','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','That\'s the frightening thing.. unless you constantly check some of this stuff, you never know when things change or will  begin to leak your info.\n\nLike in my post <a href=\"http://www.attackvector.org/?p=299\" rel=\"nofollow\">Email headers and information leaks</a>, if Google were to willy-nilly change something, it may begin to expose peoples real IP address without them even being aware of it.','2010-06-11 11:17:23','2010-06-11 16:17:23','0','252','308','','2'),(
'254','','1','Julian','188.85.100.190','j.marinov@live.com','','Hi!\nI tried something like that time ago, but the fotos in facebook have a different name. I mean, when you upload a photo there, you can download it, but the name has been changed. Probably because of smart guys like us. So my Idea was to search in google just the name of the image, which i think will do the same, but in this case I think it will be not possible.','2010-06-11 19:05:46','2010-06-12 00:05:46','0','0','308','','0');
