'257','','1','Matt','70.89.197.145','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@Julian: Actually, Tineye doesn\'t work by just using file names.  This would lead to many, many false positives and even more false negatives.  My hunch (which is only a hunch, as they don\'t make reference to their method on their \"About\" page), is that they index a file and do some kind of finger printing.  MD5, possibly?\n\nYou can see this in action by using this picture:\n\nhttp://scrapetv.com/News/News%20Pages/Business/images/bill-gates.jpg\n\nThere are 92 pictures returned.  Very few of them are named \"bill-gates.jpg\".\n\nThere\'s actually a file returned named \"ygv2a.jpg\" returned, which indicates that Tineye doesn\'t rely on the name of the file at all.','2010-06-14 09:07:04','2010-06-14 14:07:04','0','254','308','','2'),(
