'261','','1','netalien','201.243.184.43','lkernelpanic@gmail.com','http://none','Privoxy also have options to help hide whether you\'re behind a proxy or not, at the top of my head there\'s a change-x-forwarded-for to deal with the HTTP_X_FORWARDED_FOR header. Can\'t remember if HTTP_VIA is send by privoxy, but if it is, it has to have a similar option, if not, there\'s an add-header option that let\'s set arbitrary options, including \"HTTP_VIA: None your business\".','2010-06-15 18:53:45','2010-06-15 23:53:45','0','0','329','','0'),(
