'271','','1','SciFi','209.79.66.24','scifihfi@hotmail.com','','I share some of your sentiments on Lamo and I agree that this depricates wikileaks as safe channel for disclosure. However I think your argument is a little one sided. I haven\'t heard Lamo describe himself as a hacker. In fact, in Hackers Wanted he specifically said that it is not a label he identifies with. Either way it\'s somewhat of a non-issue. \n\nIn your entire criticism you don\'t mention Lamo\'s explanation-\n\nI wouldnt have done this if lives werent in danger,\n\nHe was in a war zone and basically trying to vacuum up as much classified information as he could, and just throwing it up into the air.\n\nObviously we can\'t say for sure if he was being truthful but what do you think of his explaination?','2010-06-17 14:29:00','2010-06-17 19:29:00','0','0','355','','0'),(
'272','','1','Matt','71.63.150.135','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@SciFi:  You\'re right, Lamo didn\'t describe himself, personally, as a hacker (in the documentary).. but, keep in mind, his official title is, \"the homeless hacker\", so... lol\n\nI guess my question to Lamo about possible lives being in danger are... who\'s lives?  The documents that were released involved a Blackhawk helicopter murdering unarmed journalists.. and other classified documents involving the Icesave.  Nothing has been released beyond that and based one what I\'ve read (the logs between Lamo and Manning), Lamo didn\'t really know what Manning was releasing.  None of us really know what the other documents contain, but I doubt that Assange has any real interest in leaking information about military coordinates and soldier names, addresses, etc.  Wikileaks is primarily interested in releasing information that would be considered a cover-up, inside information, or something embarrassing to governments.  I would actually lose a lot of respect for Wikileaks if Assange were to release information that did put peoples lives in danger, but I really don\'t think that\'s the goal of Wikileaks.\n\nIt will be interesting to see what other documents are released and published.\n\nI appreciate your input and you\'re right, my argument is definitely one sided and biased.  It\'s mostly based on my personal experience with Lamo and everything I\'ve seen about him beyond what I knew personally.','2010-06-17 17:43:56','2010-06-17 22:43:56','0','271','355','','2'),(
'273','','1','netalien','201.243.184.43','lkernelpanic@gmail.com','','For what I\'ve read here and there, I think that is pretty difficult to discard the \"i\'m doing it because i want to be on the news again\" thing.\n\nOne throwing another under the bus isn\'t new, it\'s a practice as old as the mind kind itself, but many decide to do it as quietly as possible, avoiding being noticed, acting with a piece of common sense, you just don\'t want everyone to know that you did what you did.\n\nWhy go and tell anyone beyond those interested on the info (feds or whatever)? Either you\'re incredible stupid or you want everyone to know that it was you, although I share the script kiddy like description, I don\'t see Lamo as a stupid person, so what\'s left? \n\nOn his reasons to disclose the leaker, one might argue that the thing about \"lives in danger\" could be a result of some paranoid issue (medical induced or otherwise), I mean, it isn\'t something you can easily discard. There\'s nothing on the logs that give some clue about what\'s in the rest of the data passed to wikileaks, the thing goes something like \"I\'ve have stuff, confidential stuff\" \"oh, I see, I think lives are in danger because of that, better tell the feds\".\n\nIn any case, I think Lamo took attributions that didn\'t concern to him, the patriot thing to me is nothing but a lame excuse because there\'s no evidence thus far that the content of that unseen data might take the lives of some, and if it\'s true that this is just because of the camera love, it\'s a very sad thing because there\'s someone that for sure is going to suffer a lot for this (i. e, Manning).','2010-06-17 18:35:25','2010-06-17 23:35:25','0','0','355','','0'),(
