'277','','1','Matt','70.89.197.145','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@dstar101:  Well, Manning came to Lamo, so Lamo didn\'t have to do any tracking.  All Lamo had to do was turn over the logs to the FBI and let the FBI do what they do.  You can read the logs <a href=\"http://www.wired.com/threatlevel/2010/06/wikileaks-chat/\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>.','2010-06-21 09:37:04','2010-06-21 14:37:04','0','274','355','','2'),(
'278','','1','Matt','70.89.197.145','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@netalien:  Amen.  If you watch the blogosphere (I hate that word).. you\'ll notice that EVERYONE is talking about Lamo again.  They\'re taking his input on security issues, wanting his opinion on policies, etc.  Check out this link: http://www.wired.com/search?query=lamo&amp;siteAlias=all&amp;x=0&amp;y=0\n\nThose are all the articles on Wired that include the word \"Lamo\".  It\'s ridiculous.  And, now, even more attention will be given to him due to this DNA controversy.\n\n\'Course, I\'m kind of fueling the fire by covering him here.  Maybe I can take advantage of the Lamo craze and profit somehow.  ;-)','2010-06-21 09:43:20','2010-06-21 14:43:20','0','273','355','','2'),(
'279','','1','netalien','201.243.184.43','lkernelpanic@gmail.com','','A clear example of misinformation, fud, media profit without common sense, people stupidity, blind slaves following what the news say...\n\nOn the same line as wired talking about his input, I found this on dailytech yesterday (you might want to edit it or remove it to avoid more ridiculous media coverage, but be sure to check it, is hilarious!):\nhttp://www.dailytech.com/ExHacker+Adrian+Lamo+Tells+Us+the+ATT+iPad+Email+Leak+is+Overblown/article18786.htm?\n\nIt\'s funny and sad at the same time how media works, you have this guy that nobody cares about being covered as some famous person whose opinion should be listen to, and people just bought it as credible.\n\nAnyway, enough of him, again, a sad situation for those involved... \n\nKeep the good work with you blog, it\'s great ;)','2010-06-21 14:47:07','2010-06-21 19:47:07','0','0','355','','0'),(
'280','','1','Matt','70.89.197.145','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@netalien:  Yeah, I came across that article too and all I had to say was, \"ugh\".  I apparently need to get arrested for something stupid and then narc on someone so I can get the same amount of street cred as Lamo.  Then I could charge magazines like Wired boatloads of money for interviews and opinions and retire in the Bahamas and drink margaritas all day.\n\nAnyone here want to share some private information with me that I could hand over to the FBI to get this ball rolling?  I\'ll send you postcards from the beach.. promise.  :-)','2010-06-22 09:21:11','2010-06-22 14:21:11','0','279','355','','2'),(
'281','','1','pablo','84.203.43.135','pablo_escobar@gmx.com','','Lamo, Poulson ..these are 2 individuals i\'ve always recognised as having little to no technical skills when it comes to hacking.\n\nThe fascination with them is still baffling..can lamo even write a basic program?\nI\'ve never seen one contribution from him in the 10 years i\'ve been following security lists.\n\nplenty of interviews though.\n\ndefinitely a media whore, there\'s no doubt there....\n\ncertainly, that\'s all i\'ll remember him for, and a snitch of course.','2010-06-27 17:32:10','2010-06-27 22:32:10','0','0','355','','0');
