'282','','1','oldschool ethics','99.155.194.240','mpineiro@linefeed.org','','The author of this post got it right the first time and should stick with his gut instinct. I can\'t believe how easy the \'hacker community\' is letting Adrian Lamo off with... I mean, is there a bigger evil-doer than the military-industrial complex of the United States to any right-minded hacker? The military is the enemy of information, they are the cointel in cointelpro, they are the ones who would take over this country if they didn\'t already run it. Almost all of your tax dollars goes to them so they can use it to bully resources into the hands of the corporations that don\'t HAVE to pay taxes because you do it for them. Remember that endless cycle?\n\nBut let\'s forget all that for a second. In Latin America, during the 20th-century military dictatorships there (the ones that just started collapsing in the mid-80s, meaning it was people in their 40s - 50s now who resisted the dictatorships in underground cells), people were outcast for ANY kind of informing. And this was during a time when fingers were being broken, electroshock torture was being used, women were being raped and impregnated by their torturers, Operation Condor, Dirty War era. Look it up if you\'ve never heard of it. And even with all that going on, people STILL were not given any leeway if they talked. You were expected to take it. Those were people who BELIEVED in something. \n\nFast forward to today. Our stupid, lazy, ironic, apathetic generation... the governments are still imprisoning innocent people, still torturing them, the CIA is still trying overthrow democratic governments that don\'t agree with them 100% and yet here comes Adrian Lamo, a snitch just to be a snitch, just to get his name to have a higher Google PageRank. And where are people to take a stand against something this low + rotten? \n\nI couldn\'t BELIEVE that Lamo went to HOPE and there were actually people defending him. What is WRONG with everybody? Meanwhile, a decent, pure-hearted 23-year-old is sitting alone in a cell in a military detention facility in Kuwait, not even aware of what\'s going on out here, probably scared to death and he\'s facing over 50 YEARS IN PRISON. He\'s 23 now -- and he\'ll be 74 YEARS OLD when/if he gets out. Because of Adrian Lamo.\n\nYeah, the kid made a mistake in trusting Lamo. But making a mistake and intentionally screwing someone over for 10 minutes of fame is a BIIIIG difference. And if you believe this garbage about \"saving lives\" ... well, you must have sand between your ears. Of course, what else is this idiot going to say? You saw that video. Who is at danger because of that? The only DANGER might be that people might realize what is going on in these ways, wise up, and actually start to care enough to DO something about it.\n\nWell, you get my point. People who are willing to give Lamo a break on this really need to get themselves correct. It\'s hard to think of something you could do lower than what he did. And he deserves to hear it, non-stop, every single day that Bradley Manning is in a jail cell.\n\nMeanwhile, you can contribute labor, money, or whatever you got to his international support group at http://www.bradleymanning.org/','2010-07-21 04:26:16','2010-07-21 09:26:16','0','0','355','','0'),(
