'315','','1','netalien','201.243.184.43','lkernelpanic@gmail.com','','Sadly, there\'s people who really don\'t care about this kind of issues but more important is how people is willing to share everything for the fun of it.\n\nSometimes I don\'t really know if we can talk about \"privacy was stolen from ...\" I mean, a huge amount of personal data is posted everywhere by the individuals this data belongs to, Joe\'s personal data can really be stolen if he decided to post it openly.\n\nIn the other hand, you can blame services who lie to users about their shared information will be kept private, but sometimes, people just don\'t care if the service actually states that all the data shared will be completely public.\n\nIn any case, much of the extortion this days is the result of people confidence, be it while clicking links blindly to get trojans installed in their systems or by sharing with someone they either know or they believe they know.\n\nOf course the lack of expertise to keep your own data safe or hidden isn\'t a valid excuse to make this way of crime less important, people still needs to care because once something is taken beyond the boundaries of your system you won\'t have the control back on your data.','2010-06-23 12:46:51','2010-06-23 17:46:51','0','0','376','','0'),(
'316','','1','Matt','70.89.197.145','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@netalien:  I think the best mindset to have when posting something on the internet is - would you mind this information being read by everyone on the internet 20 years from now?  Once Google indexes something, it never goes away.\n\nBeyond that, though, you\'re right.  People just willy-nilly clicking on stuff, installing stuff, etc. opens up major holes.  In fact, that\'s how Mijangos infected these women.  He uploaded a file, which appeared to be a popular song, to some kind of peer-to-peer service (I\'m going to go out on a limb and guess Limewire).  The women didn\'t bother to check the file, they just clicked on it.\n\nWhich, actually, just gave me an idea for a new post.  ;-)','2010-06-23 13:28:08','2010-06-23 18:28:08','0','315','376','','2'),(
