'334','','1','Erik','153.9.5.205','hortonew@gmail.com','http://n/a','great post. what are your thoughts on using 1 very secure password wherever you go? or slight variations of it?  obviously, if you stumble upon a poorly created site that doesn\'t do a hash of it, and someone takes their database, they have your lovely password in clear text.  Or if someone\'s got a keylogger, it\'s all over as well.  Just kind of curious what you do (maybe use a secure one for legit traffic, and a throwaway password for the iffy-sites.  That\'s kinda where I\'m at now).','2010-06-28 16:02:37','2010-06-28 21:02:37','0','0','397','','0'),(
'335','','1','Matt','70.89.197.145','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@Erik:  Well, honestly.. my issue with using just one really secure password is that how often do you register with a website (even a large, popular one that should know better (AHEM.. ezinearticles.com)) and they send you an email with your username and password in clear text?\n\nWhen that happens, I begin to wonder how many boxes along the emails route were compromised and sniffing.\n\nIt\'s idiotic that they do that and it drives me nuts when I come across it.  My two huge pet peeves on the internet are:\n\n1) Sending passwords through email\n2) People who send an email to a large group and use CC instead of BCC.  I actually like it when companies do this, though.  I usually email them back and say something like, \"Awesome.. thanks for your customer list..\"  I mean, if they\'re stupid enough to leak it, I might as well use it for something.. competitors will pay a lot to have a list of customers from another company.  ;-)\n\nWe\'re passed the point of education.. now it\'s time for punishment.\n\nI guess I kind of got off topic a bit.. but.. do I have a perfect password policy myself?  No.. I have 3 or 4 ten alpha-numeric passwords that I use for the important sites.. and then I have really lame passwords for sites that I don\'t care about.  If I register at a website that emails me my password back to me in clear text, I change that password at all of the sites that I used that password on, which is a pain and a very tedious process, which is why it drives me nuts when that happens.','2010-06-29 09:23:57','2010-06-29 14:23:57','0','334','397','','2');
