'345','','1','Sie','20.138.1.245','vickers.j.simon@sky.com','','Just drive to the nearest town, pop into a coffee shop and it can bet there are at least 5-10 wireless networks within range that you could use!\n\nIf you really want to be an arse then exploit some poor sods laptop who is reading the news sites while having his coffee then use that connection to the coffee shops wireless, through tor and it becomes MUCH more difficult to be tracked. Not that I condone hacking innocents.\n\nAs for using WPA I smile everytime I walk into a few pubs and see \"Todays Wireless code is....\" written on a chalk board or the like. =)\n\nMatt, I heard previously about network cards still sending some form of a signature even if you alter the MAC address, I just haven\'t had time to look into it. Have you come across anything like this?','2010-06-30 05:00:59','2010-06-30 10:00:59','0','0','401','','0'),(
'346','','1','Matt','70.89.197.145','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@Sie:  Yeah, there are so many ways to get through wireless \"security\" that it isn\'t even funny.. lol\n\nI actually have not encountered anything unusual taking place after spoofing a MAC address using any of the cards that I have.  I do know that I\'ve had issues actually using macspoof on a few different cards, but that was the extent of it.\n\nOne other thing I should have mentioned.. don\'t use your embedded NIC when doing something like this.  Spend the $30 and go get a USB wireless card.  Pay for it with cash.  I don\'t know for sure that this is taking place, but if you were to hack something and your MAC address was found.. it would be theoretically possible for the feds backtrack to the manufacturer, find out which store the card was sold to, then do a cross reference using the store records to find the credit card that was used to purchase the card.  So, buy it in person, at a store not right next to your house, and use cash.  Probably overly paranoid, but I know that when the feds decide to do their job, for whatever reason, it\'s amazing what they\'re able to pull off.','2010-06-30 08:56:15','2010-06-30 13:56:15','0','345','401','','2'),(
