'370','','1','Dan','95.172.224.122','dan3@yopmail.com','','Truecrypt calls it `plausible deniability` - what\'s so good about it is that there only way to *prove* that a hidden volume exists is to have the password/keyfile for it. Since the law enforcement agencies can\'t prove it exists, they can\'t legally force you to give up the password - refusing to do so is an offence in some countries - so you\'re safe.','2010-06-30 11:11:55','2010-06-30 16:11:55','0','0','420','','0'),(
