'412','','1','Matt','70.89.197.145','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@strcmp:  I get that.. but my concerns would be:\n\n1) Who\'s providing the patch?\n2) Can the provider be trusted?\n3) Do they provide the source code of the patch?\nAnd, ultimately.. 4) Is this thing a backdoor?\n\nTo be honest, in most circumstances, I would say using a 3rd party patch to fix this problem might expose you to more risks than not patching it at all.','2010-07-27 10:07:31','2010-07-27 15:07:31','0','411','457','','2'),(
