'462','','1','PicPaste','94.249.226.1','contact@sectoor.de','http://picpaste.com','Hi,\n\nthanks for bringing so \"much\" attention to our service PicPaste. We\'re aware of your script and stuff and could also start blocking tor, if we want. But we want to offer a free service, which enables easy and stable sharing of pictures. This also means (at least for us) that we want ppl to access \"anonymously\" the pictures, so blocking tor would kill this intention.\nPicPaste was build as a easy to use service, to allow ppl to upload a picture and tell other ppl the url, like on phone. For that reason we choose a simple code to avoid some \"long stupid\" urls. This was at least good for about 5 years now.\nToday we pushed a new feature which enables ppl to add a random string or complete obscure the picture name, to avoid simple guessing like you used.\nWe\'ll keep up this service as long as ppl are happy and using it, but we\'ll not put manpower on fix every \"boring script work\"-load out there.\n\nSo, at least for us, we have finished our work \"against\" such attacks. Those attacks are attacks on our users, not our service directly, as you try to get their pictures without permission. This was the reason for us to block your script, and will block such attemps in future.\n\nHopefully you understand that we\'re not interested in a \"code war\". So it would be nice if you just leave it \"as is\" and enjoy the stuff you already grabbed.\n\nRegards,\nThe PicPaste Service ;)','2010-08-17 14:43:01','2010-08-17 19:43:01','0','0','487','','0'),(
