'464','','1','Matt','70.89.197.145','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@PicPaste:  I understand where you\'re coming from and appreciate the fact that your service isn\'t littered with ads, popups, etc. as all the other picture sharing services.  And, the underlying point of this post was not necessarily to cause you problems, but to point out the overall problems that we come across on the internet when people (designers/programmers) focus more on the end result without putting much attention in to the ways services can be abused, hacked, or manipulated.\n\nSo, at your request, I\'ll discontinue updating the script any further because I feel the point of my post has been relayed pretty clearly...\n\nMy only question to you, though, is.. why not make the random string a default option?  Considering that most people simply copy &amp; paste the url in to an email, IM, whatever.. a few character random string shouldn\'t really cause too much trouble.  Then allow people to turn the feature off if they care to.\n\nAnyway, thank you for a civil response to my post/script and I hope that it didn\'t cause you too much of a headache.  ;-)','2010-08-17 14:54:22','2010-08-17 19:54:22','0','462','487','','2'),(
'465','','1','PicPaste','94.249.226.1','contact@sectoor.de','http://picpaste.com','@Matt\n\nWe plan to do so. But for now we\'ll just take a look how this feature will be accepted. It was a long planned feature, so it was more or less just a quick switch to enable it for us.\nWe don\'t want to change to much for the ppl who use the service. But it seems that the feature is beeing accepted by the users and we also regognize the setting, so an user just has to set it once and will be automaticly get the same setting in future.\nIf no problems will be reported so far, we\'ll make the \"easy\" setting the default in the next days.\n\nRegards,\nPicPaste :)','2010-08-17 15:00:26','2010-08-17 20:00:26','0','0','487','','0'),(
