'525','','1','dehaul','192.101.136.224','dehaul@gmail.com','','I used to have this opinion when I was \"younger\" in my development as a computer nerd software developer. The thing is, I have discovered it is actually *very* hard to produce software that works properly, on time, and on budget. \n\nSeriously, Linux has had all sorts of vulnerabilities:\n\nhttp://www.google.com/search?q=linux+remote+kernel+vuln\n\nPlus you have just downright stupid bugs like the Debian SSH vuln from about a year ago where the developer messed with working code and broke it.\n\nAdditionally, your comparison is really not fair to Microsoft as all the market forces are driving nefarious individuals to attacking Windows since it is the best bang for the exploit (PLUS all us computer geeks like to attack Microsoft because they are the \"bad guy\").\n\nGood, solid, large scale software is just freaking hard to build. I remember fondly our first family computer back before windows even existed running MS DOS. Microsoft\'s real value is that they took this niche hobby of \"computing\" and brought it to the world... give em a little more credit!','2010-09-08 15:33:09','2010-09-08 20:33:09','0','0','573','','0'),(
