'530','','1','Matt','75.72.21.51','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@dehaul:  Yeah.. 89% of desktop users is a hard number to argue with, I\'ll give you that.. lol\n\nI think whats going to happen, though, which is already proving to be somewhat true (as proof with your wife, my wife to be, and my mom), Ubuntu, specifically, will begin to gain even more popularity as these problems continue to rise.  I held out for a LONG time to move to Ubuntu because I didn\'t like how user friendly it was.  I didn\'t like package management, nor did I like the GUI interface.  I was a hardcore Linux geek.. only used the terminal.. then I got older and noticed that I was spending a lot of unnecessary time downloading dependencies, manually maintaining the OS, etc. and made the switch from Slackware to Ubuntu.  I wanted to hate it, but I just can\'t.. I love it.  :-D\n\nThe Linux vs. Windows argument is ages old and will continue until either Linux or Windows (or both) are dead.  But, I am definitely happy to see people switching to Linux and people beginning to know what it is.','2010-09-10 18:22:46','2010-09-10 23:22:46','0','529','573','','2'),(
