'551','','1','Matt','70.89.197.145','matt@attackvector.org','http://www.attackvector.org','@pentest09:  Thanks for the video.. but, I don\'t think it\'s a matter of there being some confusion over it working or not.. in some instances, it simply just doesn\'t work, and from my experience thus far with this exploit, it seems to be more often than not that it doesn\'t work.\n\nExample:\n\nWindows XP SP2 w/ Adobe Reader 9.3.0 fail.  Adobe crashes, indicating a fault in the cooltype.dll, but no session created regardless of how long it sits there.. and it sits there for quite some time. \nWindows XP SP2 w/ Adobe Reader 8.2.0 fail.\nWindows XP SP3 w/ Adobe Reader 9.3.0 fail.\nWindows XP SP3 w/ Adobe Reader 8.2.0 fail.\nWindows XP SP2 w/ Adobe Reader 8.2.4 fail.\nWindows XP SP3 w/ Adobe Reader 8.2.4 fail.\nWindows XP SP2 w/ Adobe Reader 9.3.4 success.\nWindows XP SP3 w/ Adobe Reader 9.3.4 success.\n\nSo, from what I\'ve experienced personally, this specifically targets 9.3.4 (which is indicated in the advisory), but unlike the advisory, I have not been able to get it to succeed on any earlier versions of Adobe.\n\nAlso, for what its worth, the 9.3.4 version that I used was a fresh copy just downloaded from Adobe\'s website, so they haven\'t patched it yet.','2010-09-15 10:13:47','2010-09-15 15:13:47','0','550','579','','2'),(
