'583','','1','H. Carvey','96.255.15.232','keydet89@yahoo.com','http://windowsir.blogspot.com','Very cool!  I use something very similar in my most recent book (sadly, won\'t be out until 15 Feb 2011) on Registry analysis; specifically, by getting the BSSID and MAC address for a WAP from the Registry, you can perform geolocation using SkyHook.\n\nI\'ve mentioned that LE could use this...for example, determine that a suspect (by analyzing his computer) was in a particular location, then interview regulars in the area (baristas, etc.) or view security video footage.  I even got a comment to one post on the topic that someone was able to determine that an employee had been to a competitor\'s location for an interview when they took vacation.  ;-)','2010-09-28 06:16:25','2010-09-28 11:16:25','0','0','613','','0'),(
