'611','','1','Wicky','77.44.41.159','wicky@4armed.com','','Useful post as always. The first thing which struck me was finding out if I had any historical hits on these sites.  I knocked up a very crude bash loop which should help. Feel free to tart it up a bit:\n\nfor x in `egrep -v \'^#|^$\' /etc/squid/zeus.txt`; do \n echo \"--$x--\" &gt;&gt; /tmp/zeus.log; \n grep \"$x\" /var/log/squid/access.log &gt;&gt; /tmp/zeus.log; \ndone\n\nThis (hopefully obviously) will produce a file at /tmp/zeus.log which will contain a line printing out each line of the zeus.txt file pre/app-ended with -- and under that will be any matching lines found in your Squid access log.  \n\nA quick way to find out if you\'ve got a problem is obviously:\n\ngrep -v ^-- /tmp/zeus.log\n\nwhich should return nothing if you\'re all clean. :-)','2011-03-15 06:17:15','2011-03-15 11:17:15','0','0','633','','0'),(
