'625','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:12.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/12.0','1','Bobby','69.90.230.230','bobby@attackvector.org','','Hi Fouad,\r\n\r\nThank you :-)\r\n\r\nFor the problem you mentioned, it\'s because I\'m using a script from BlockScript.com to block users coming from hosting network IPs, anonymous proxies, Tor, etc.  The reason for this is that most people that attack a site usually come through these sources.  Right now I have most of that blocked and white-listed the IPs from my VPN services.  \r\n\r\nIf it becomes a hassle, I\'ll turn it off but so far it\'s been helpful for me.\r\n\r\nBobby','2012-05-07 16:38:32','2012-05-07 16:38:32','0','624','658','','3'),(
