'501','2','open','http://www.attackvector.org/?p=501','0','open','','2','I came across this today and haven\'t had a chance yet to play around with it, but it sounds too good to be true.  Apparently this package contains a number of tools that target bluetooth devices.  The list includes:\n\n<pre>\n* Blueper - used to transfer files to and from a BT device\n* BlueSnarf - used to steal files from a BT device\n* Bluetooth Stack Smasher - looks like it attempts a number of different attack methods against BT devices\n* Carwhisperer - turn a BT headset into a listening device\n* psm_scan, rfcomm_scan - part of the BT Audit suite\n* vcardblaster - a BT DoS application\n</pre>\n<p></p>\nAnyway, it looks like something fun to play with.  If you try it out before I do, let me know how it turns out.  You can download the file <a href=\"http://www.attackvector.org/files/pwntooth-0.2.3.tar.gz\">here</a>','','2010-08-20 10:45:38','2010-08-20 15:45:38','','','2010-08-20 10:45:38','2010-08-20 15:45:38','pwntooth-bluetooth-pwnership','0','','publish','Pwntooth - Bluetooth pwnership.','post',''),(
